is remarkable\ngroup at\nsth Delafield N.W.\nJust around the corner from\nSherman Circle on the highest\npoint in Petworth, facing south.\nThey are the most com\nplete and perfect Homes\nthat have ever been offered\nin Washington at anything\nlike this price, and the\nmore carefully you inspect\nand the more critical you\nare, the stronger will be\nthe urge to own and live\nin one.\n6 big rooms; 3 big\nporches; hardwood floors;\ntile bath with 'built-in tub\nand shower; big coat closet\nwith mirror door on the\nfirst floor; wardrobe\nclosets in every bed room;\nbig brick pantry; hot\nwater heat; automatic\nheater and storage tank.\nThe lot is of excellent\nsize with plenty of room\nfor garage.\n\u20197,950\nSSOO Cash, $69.50 a Month\nThis means that of the\n169.50 more than half\napplies to the purchase of\nthe house, while it will not\ncost you in incidental\ncharges, which are the\nequivalent of rent, S3O a\nmonth to live in it while\nyou are buying it\nOpen for inspection from\n9 a. m. to 9 p. m.\nEither ear line. Itth St. but. or we\n\u00abIU send an aoto\nCAFRIT2\n\u00a9wners and Builders of Commu\u00dflttea\n14th 4 K M. 9080\n(Initials).\n81. I conquered\n(Latin).\n83. Wanda\n55. Away.\n57. Utter deetrue\ntlon.\n\u25bcEBTICAL\n1. An outweigh\ning.\n9. Navigate.\n8. Incorporated\n(abbr.).\n4. Lieutenant\n(abbr.).\n5. Raises\nt. Pillar of a\nwinding stair\ncase.\n7. Neuter pro\nnoun.\nt. Rabble.\n9. Burden. 1\n10. Suffocation.\n14. A kind of rub-\nber tree.\n17. Strap of a\nbridle.\n19. Pertaining to\na union of\nStatea\n21. Allure.\n24. Sun god.\n25. Eacort.\n26. Point of com\npose.\n29. Comparative\nsuffix.\n31. Name of a\nmonth (abbr.).\n34. Ascend.\n15. Overcharge\n(abbr.).\n87. Point of com-\n38. Electrical\n(abbr.).\n4L Solid glass with\ntriangular\nends.\nSolution To Monday Puzzle\nC|A T Os|A LOF TMS HAM\nA V\u00a3W|L 6W\u00a3 RB c AW S\nDETE RM|l N e\u00dfh O. rK\u00ae\nrR e\u00dfe O Nfs\u00dfP ELT S J\nBBBF A Nfsfl\u00df E A D|s|\nh E 5 A l 5JBfo a l sMd|o\nA A R MBD]O|O R S|hA p\nD_ A F TBF EI N t\u00dfc AR\u00a3\nE N T H R ALL Sgh|A VEN\nS dB O T A S A R|E S S\nMjT N _L A YB c UR T MHO\nHa ng e l\u00dfp i p eH e b lb|\nR I \u00a3A SpPE D O MjE T E R\ni d|o l\u00dfh o\u2019te l\u00dfa n t e\nm[et eB^ p JL r a\u00df r aa d\ntry. They may not necessarily seU\nmore cars, but\u2019 they have the best\nopportunity ever presented to\nstabilize their business and to estab\nlish themselves securely for the\nfuture.\n\u201cIn this connection. I am preach\ning to them the doctrine of scien\ntific merchandising. We have had\nplenty of science in the design and\nmanufacture of automtfolle. We\nstill have need for more science in\nselling them.\n\u201cThe automobile business has also\nreached what might be termed the\n\u2018service era.\u2019 Gradually it is de\nveloping the elements of greater\ncourtesy tnd consideration toward\ncar owners; better equipped service\nstations; efficient accounting sys\ntems and honesty In advertising.\nFor instance, In reference to adver\n-1 Using; while we manufacture six\ncylinder cars we make them stand\nupon their own merits Instead of\nboosting them by invidious compari\nsons with the fours or making\nderogatory comment upon the\neights.\"\nMr. Glancy stated that the 1927\nproduction of his factories will be\nabout 200,000 units. He emphasized,\nas Illustrative of the industry\u2019s sta\nbility, that the Oakland is not inter\nested in selling 200,000 cars merely\nfor the purpose of making a record.\nWould Avoid Overproduction\n\"I wish to build and sell only the\nnumber of cars which can be han\ndled at a profit to our dealers and\nourselves,\u201d he declared.\nMr. Glancy takes issue with those\nwho predict a European trend In\nAmerican cars. He asserted that\n\u201cthe shoe is on the other foot,\u201d and\nthat European manufacturers are\nlearning from America not only how\nto design but also how to produce\nmotor cars.\nNEW LOW\nPRICES\non\nInside-Frosted\nEDISON\nMAZDA\nBULBS\nBULBS\n6 for $1.38\nBULBS\n6 for $1.50\n100-Wt. Bulbs, 40c\nIMUDDIMANi\n709 13th, Main 140\nOVERLANDS IN\nBIG DEMAND\nTOLEDO, Ohio, April B.\u2014The in\nflux of orders received by Willys-\nOverland since the new models were\nfirst announced in January con\ntinues unabated with indications\nthat March will establish a new\nrecord for shipments over the same\nmonth of all previous years. This\nis based on the number of W, hippets,\nWillys-Knights and Whippet sixes\nthat have been shipped up .to March\n28, the total being 81 per cent\ngreater than the same period of last\nyear.\nNot only is the month showing a\nmarked increase over March of 1926,\nbut the car shipments from January\nup to date show an increase of 16\nper cent over the same period of\n1926. This percentage of increase\nis constantly rising, showing that\nthe Toledo manufacturer is well\nalong on the way toward reaching\nthe 800,000 car quota set for the\ncurrent year.\nAnother outstanding factor, which\nindicates a continued high car pro\nduction at Willys-Overland plant, is\nincreased amount of raw materials\nbeing received daily. For the month\nof March the receipt of raw ma\nterials shows an incerase of more\nthan 80 per cent over March of last\nyear.\n49. Put In an urn.\n45. Portion.\n41. I aaw (Latin).\n50. A deer.\n52. Largo tub.\n54. Debtor (abbr.).\nSt. On account\n(abbr.).\nNA S H\nLeads the World in Motor Car Value\nthe\ndown payment on a Four\n\u2014andgetaNash\nNash6-cyfimhr 9 instrument board\u2014an inefepensabfe conwmence.\novff, more 4-cylinder performance. 5 Budd-Micbefin steel disc wheels; Alemite high\nYou can buy a Nash Light Sx enclosed car for pressure chassis hibrication* instead of\nas little as $925 Lo. h. factory\u2014an amazingly low ioned grease cups,\nprice for a car like this. cleaner and oil filter to seal the engine against\nFor besides the exceptional smoothness of Nash dirt; steering gear especially engineered to handle\n6-cylinder, 7-bearing performance, the new Light ballo